description:
EO 26-04 orders all cabinet-level state agencies and state boards or commissions that issue permits to perform a comprehensive review of their processes relating to permits, licenses, certifications, or other  regulatory approvals to identify opportunities to improve such processes. The Executive Order also encourages the usage of technology such as AI and online dashboards or portals. State bodies must compile their findings in a "Improvement Plan" to the Office of the Governor that specifies: 
- Specific process improvements;
- Any legislative changes needed to implement recommendations;
- Any rule changes needed to implement recommendations;
- A timeline for implementation; and
- Performance metrics such as average turnaround time.
